I felt it was a bit pricey, however--for this money I could have stayed at the 4-star Carlton, or my usual favorite, the Affinia Shelburne, also in the area and more luxurious.	This is our preferred accommodation when we are in the city.	Overall if your purpose is tourism and your main need is a reasonable but confy room, then you're in the right place.	I agree that this accommodation can not be compared with a big five star fancy new hotel, and the furniture is from the eighties, but the price is very reasonable and I find the suites extremely comfortable.